The HTML mark up produced by this template includes an [[HCalendar|hCalendar microformat]], which makes the event/ date details [[Parsing|parsable]] by computers, either acting automatically to catalogue article across Wikipedia, or via a browser tool operated by a person, to (for example) add the subject to a calendar or diary application. For more information about the use of [[microformat]]s on Wikipedia, please see [[WP:UF|the microformat project]].

hCalendar uses HTML classes including:

{{Flatlist|
*attendee
*description
*dtend
*dtstart
*location
*summary
*url
*vevent
}}

